---
import DarkLayout from '../layouts/DarkLayout.astro';
---

<DarkLayout title="NulX | Offensive Security">
  <div class="mb-12 flex flex-col md:flex-row justify-between items-start md:items-center gap-6">
    <div>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-black uppercase tracking-tighter mb-2">&gt; VANSH_KALAWATIA</h1>
      <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold opacity-80 border-b-2 border-[#00ff00] inline-block pb-1">Independent Security Researcher | github.com/Nulx0x00</p>
    </div>
    <a href="/" class="border-2 border-[#00ff00] px-4 py-2 font-bold uppercase hover:bg-[#00ff00] hover:text-black transition-colors flex items-center gap-2 flex-shrink-0 shadow-[4px_4px_0_0_#00ff00] active:translate-y-1 active:shadow-none">
      <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-5 w-5" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor">
        <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M9.707 14.707a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 010-1.414l4-4a1 1 0 011.414 1.414L7.414 9H15a1 1 0 110 2H7.414l2.293 2.293a1 1 0 010 1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
      </svg>
      Return to Light
    </a>
  </div>

  <div class="space-y-16">
    <!-- SUMMARY -->
    <section class="border-l-4 border-[#00ff00] pl-6 py-2">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-black uppercase mb-4 opacity-70">/* Summary */</h2>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">
        3rd-year Cyber Security undergraduate with hands-on offensive security skills across web application penetration testing, network reconnaissance, and vulnerability assessment. Built NulX Port Scanner — a production-quality multi-threaded Java tool with a measurable 97% performance improvement. Practised OWASP Top 10 exploitation via DVWA, PortSwigger, HTB, and THM. Actively seeking a Cyber Security internship to apply practical red-team and security assessment skills within a real engineering team.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- ARSENAL (SKILLS) -->
    <section>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-black uppercase mb-6 opacity-70">/* Arsenal */</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div class="border border-[#00ff00] p-6 hover:bg-[#00ff00]/5 transition-colors">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-xl mb-4 border-b border-[#00ff00]/30 pb-2">Security</h3>
          <p>Penetration Testing, Web App Security, Vuln Assessment, Enumeration, Port Scanning, Exploitation, OWASP Top 10, SQLi, XSS, IDOR, CSRF, Auth Bypass, SSRF</p>
        </div>
        <div class="border border-[#00ff00] p-6 hover:bg-[#00ff00]/5 transition-colors">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-xl mb-4 border-b border-[#00ff00]/30 pb-2">Tools</h3>
          <p>Burp Suite (Proxy, Repeater, Intruder, Decoder), Nmap, Wireshark, Metasploit, OWASP ZAP, Netcat, DVWA, Kali Linux, VirtualBox</p>
        </div>
        <div class="border border-[#00ff00] p-6 hover:bg-[#00ff00]/5 transition-colors">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-xl mb-4 border-b border-[#00ff00]/30 pb-2">Programming & Networking</h3>
          <p>Python, Java, Bash | TCP/IP, DNS, HTTP/HTTPS, OSI Model, Socket Programming</p>
        </div>
        <div class="border border-[#00ff00] p-6 hover:bg-[#00ff00]/5 transition-colors">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-xl mb-4 border-b border-[#00ff00]/30 pb-2">Compliance</h3>
          <p>India DPDP Act 2023 (PII discovery), NIST framework</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- OPERATIONS -->
    <section>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-black uppercase mb-6 opacity-70">/* Operations */</h2>
      
      <div class="space-y-8">
        <div class="border-2 border-[#00ff00] p-6 sm:p-8 hover:bg-[#00ff00]/5 transition-colors shadow-[8px_8px_0_0_#00ff00]">
          <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row justify-between sm:items-center mb-4 gap-2">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-black">Independent Security Researcher</h3>
            <span class="border border-[#00ff00] px-3 py-1 text-sm font-bold bg-[#00ff00]/10">Nov 2024 - Present</span>
          </div>
          <p class="font-bold mb-4 border-b border-[#00ff00]/30 inline-block pb-1">NulX Security | Jaipur, Rajasthan (Remote)</p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-3 opacity-90 leading-relaxed mt-2">
            <li>Built <span class="font-bold">NulX Port Scanner</span> (Java) reducing scan time for 1,000 ports from 36s to 1.1s (97% improvement).</li>
            <li>Practised OWASP Top 10 exploitation across DVWA and PortSwigger (SQLi, XSS, CSRF, IDOR).</li>
            <li>Completed active labs on Hack The Box and TryHackMe (enumeration, privilege escalation).</li>
            <li>Published comparative security research on sequential vs. concurrent network scanning architectures.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- PROJECTS -->
    <section>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-black uppercase mb-6 opacity-70">/* Projects */</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <a href="https://github.com/Nulx0x00/NulX-Port-Scanner" target="_blank" class="block border border-[#00ff00] p-6 hover:bg-[#00ff00]/10 transition-all cursor-pointer">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2 flex justify-between items-center">
            NulX Port Scanner
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-5 w-5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M10 6H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v10a2 2 0 002 2h10a2 2 0 002-2v-4M14 4h6m0 0v6m0-6L10 14" />
            </svg>
          </h3>
          <p class="text-sm opacity-80 mb-4 text-[#00ff00]/70">Java • Multithreading • Socket Programming</p>
          <p class="opacity-90">Multi-threaded TCP port scanner reducing scan time by 97%. Configurable threading options designed around the recon phase of a pentest.</p>
        </a>
        <div class="block border border-[#00ff00] p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Research: Concurrent Network Scanning</h3>
          <p class="text-sm opacity-80 mb-4 text-[#00ff00]/70">Java • Concurrency • Tech Writing</p>
          <p class="opacity-90">Published findings on LinkedIn and GitHub regarding speed advantages of multithreaded scanning for attackers and detection windows for defenders.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- TRAINING & CERTS -->
    <section>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-black uppercase mb-6 opacity-70">/* Training Grounds */</h2>
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="border-l-2 border-dashed border-[#00ff00] pl-6 py-2 hover:bg-[#00ff00]/5 transition-colors">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold">Hack The Box & TryHackMe</h3>
          <p class="opacity-90 mt-2">Completed Beginner-tier machines via SMB, FTP, SSH, HTTP. Linux privesc via SUID binaries. Completed 5+ paths including Offensive Security & SOC Level 1.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="border-l-2 border-dashed border-[#00ff00] pl-6 py-2 hover:bg-[#00ff00]/5 transition-colors">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold">PortSwigger Web Security Academy</h3>
          <p class="opacity-90 mt-2">Apprentice-level labs on SQLi, XSS, auth vulnerabilities, IDOR, path traversal using Burp Suite Proxy/Repeater.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="border-l-2 border-dashed border-[#00ff00] pl-6 py-2 hover:bg-[#00ff00]/5 transition-colors">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold">Certifications (Planned)</h3>
          <p class="opacity-90 mt-2">Google Cybersecurity Professional Certificate (Expected Sep 2026)</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
    
    <div class="text-center pt-12 pb-24 opacity-50 text-sm">
      <p>EOF</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</DarkLayout>
